104. Formulate a PHP program to open a text file and print the nth line in the text file if then'th line
does not exist print 'no data'.
<?php
$filename = "sample.txt"; // Text file name
$n = 3; // Change this to the line number you want to print (nth line)

// Check if file exists
if (file_exists($filename)) {
    // Read the file into an array (each line as an element)
    $lines = file($filename, FILE_IGNORE_NEW_LINES | FILE_SKIP_EMPTY_LINES);

    // Check if nth line exists
    if (isset($lines[$n - 1])) {
        echo "Line $n: " . $lines[$n - 1];
    } else {
        echo "No data";
    }
} else {
    echo "File not found!";
}
?>
